Simple steps to install ubuntu on windows11 using microsoft store.

https://chat.openai.com/share/e8eee752-6f3c-4ee9-b6f1-fd75cd7a6f43

Issue:   
Failed to attach disk 'C:\Users\<User>\AppData\Local\Packages\CanonicalGroupLimited.Ubuntu_79rhkp1fndgsc\LocalState\ext4.vhdx' to WSL2: The system cannot find the file specified.
Error code: Wsl/Service/CreateInstance/MountVhd/ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND

Fix: 
List the distributions installed, by running following in PowerShell.  #:  wsl -l

Unregister the distribution. Replace the "Ubuntu" below with your distribution name found in Step #:    wsl --unregister Ubuntu

Launch the Ubuntu (or other distribution) which was installed using Microsoft Store
